args: All right, my turn now. I rolled...a seven!\nI'm moving my light infantry forward!
Trying to fend me off with a magician, eh?\nWell played, Sam!
But I saw that coming, which is why\nI've got an assassin waiting for you.
I'm coming for you now!\nI rolled a ten, and I'm charging foward\nwith my light infantry!
Ha! Your commander is down,\nwhich means I win!
Whew! Talk about a heated battle.\nYou're really fun to play with, Sam.
...Oh hey, it's raining. Rain always makes\nme think of the day I first found you.
(We were busy getting ready for\nthe summer festival at the time...)
Ugh, it's the one-woman idiot brigade.
I will do no such thing, young man!\nYou must help with the preparations!
No I must NOT! Stop trying to force\na bunch of crap on me, gosh!
Festivals are stupid. If you want one,\ngo set it up your own dang self.
How dare you call my perfectly planned,\nspectacular-in-every-way festival ＂dumb!＂
I have had ENOUGH of this!\nMark my words, this will be\nthe day I get you to wo—
L-look! Up there! It's a flying lion,\nand he's breathing FIRE!
Hey! Return here this INSTANT, Eugene!
I'm finally rid of her. What a pain...
Why should I help out at festivals\nthat have nothing to do with me?
Those things are no fun if you go alone,\nso I'm gonna stay home this year, too.
Huh? Why's it raining when it's still sunny?
H-hey! Who's there?! You better not\nbe eavesdropping on me!
Huh. It's making a sound like an animal,\nbut it's not a cat or a dog or anything...
Oh, geez. Whatever it is,\nit seems really young...
I don't see anything else here.\nNo friends or family or whatever.
Guess you're alone just like me, huh?
You wanna come with me, then?
Hey, this thing seems really happy!\nWait, does it understand what I'm saying?
Well, if I can talk to it,\nI'd better give it a name.
Hmm... You know what?\nYou seem like a Sam to me.
Heh. You like that, huh? In that case,\nit's nice to meet you, Sam!
(In the end, it turned out Sam was so\nsmart we could even play board games.)
(Sam was understanding, calming,\nand the best friend a guy could want.)
(Then the day of the festival came...)

You sit about feeling bad for yourself,
and on the rare occasions you speak,
naught by gloom flows out! Little wonder
you're so cut off from the world.
Oh yeah, like people enjoy having some\negocentric hag boss 'em around all the\ntime! Yak yak yak, that's you!
I absolutely HATE you, young man!\nI absolutely HATE you, lady!
(Because Catherine and I fought,\nSam changed. We had to mend\nfences in order to stop the chaos.)
(But just saying we were friends wasn't\nenough—we needed to get to know one\nanother and resolve our differences.)
(That led me to find out how her frustration\ninfluenced her attitude, and how hard she\nworked as a result.)
Sam ended up teaching me\nsomething really important.
Everyone has their own worries\nand issues to deal with.
I want to change. I NEED to change. \nI thought I'd made up my mind about that,\nbut now I'm just running away again!
Things can't keep going on like this.\nI know that. But...
But I'm just so darn NERVOUS! I mean,\ncan I really fit in at the Halidom?
Hmm? Hey, where are you going?\nThat's the front door.
Why's he jumping up and down\nin front of the door like that?
Wait... Are you trying to cheer me on and\nhelp me move forward? Like, ＂Let's open\nthis door and head back to the Halidom!＂?
Aw, thanks, Sam. I feel a bit more\ncourageous now. ...Just a little.
But that little bit is enough to pick myself\nup and try again!
